Greetings from Los Angeles and welcome back to In the Room, my
twice-weekly private email on the media.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

In tonight=E2=80=99s email, news and notes on Rebecca Kutler=E2=80=99s asce=
nsion to the top job at MSNBC, which is about to be spun off into the wilde=
rness as the crown jewel of Comcast=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CSpinCo.=E2=80=9D Her=
 appointment will not change the cable network=E2=80=99s long-term fate, bu=
t it may make things interesting again.

=C2=A0

Also mentioned in this email: Will Lewis, Wendy McMahon, Rachel Maddow, Rya=
n Lizza, Rashida Jones, Jay Sures, Jack Blanchard, Jonathan Greenblatt, Chr=
is Licht, Alex Wagner, Shari Redstone, and many, many more=E2=80=A6=C2=A0

=C2=A0

But first=E2=80=A6

* =F0=9F=8D=B8 The Grill Room: On the latest edition of the podcast, long-t=
enured tech reporter=E2=80=94and Musk confidant=E2=80=94Ashlee Vance joined=
 me to discuss his new media startup, Core Memory, and the high-risk, high-=
reward leap from legacy media into entrepreneurship. We also address the tr=
ansformative potential of A.I. and the interplay between tech C.E.O.s and T=
rump. Follow on
Apple ( https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/the-grill-room/id1775515432?u=
tm_campaign=3DIn+the+Room+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F15%2F25%29&utm_content=3DIn+=
