* WaPo=E2=80=99s Gang of 400: More than 400 journalists at
The Washington Post have signed a letter to Jeff Bezos pleading with him to=
 come to the office and address their concerns over the paper=E2=80=99s dir=
ection under publisher and C.E.O. Will Lewis. =E2=80=9CWe are deeply alarme=
d by recent leadership decisions that have led readers to question the inte=
grity of this institution, broken with a tradition of transparency, and pro=
mpted some of our most distinguished colleagues to leave,=E2=80=9D they wri=
te in
the letter, which was first revealed by NPR=E2=80=99s David Folkenflik. =E2=
=80=9CWe understand the need for change and we are eager to deliver the new=
s in innovative ways. But we need a clear vision we can believe in.=E2=80=
=9D Not great, Will!

Now, I imagine the centibillionaire entrepreneur, who is currently trying t=
o launch ( https://apnews.com/article/rocket-launch-blue-origin-jeff-bezos-=
0cb070fa51356f3720c3477ca9fb670b?utm_campaign=3DIn+the+Room+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%=
281%2F15%2F25%29&utm_content=3DIn+The+Room+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F15%2F25%29&=
utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42a=
bd12a ) a
rocket larger than the Statue of Liberty and preparing ( https://www.nbcnew=
s.com/politics/donald-trump/elon-musk-jeff-bezos-mark-zuckerberg-attend-tru=
mp-inauguration-rcna187642?utm_campaign=3DIn+the+Room+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F=
15%2F25%29&utm_content=3DIn+The+Room+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F15%2F25%29&utm_me=
dium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a =
) to attend next week=E2=80=99s Trump inauguration alongside Elon Musk, Tim=
 Cook, and Mark Zuckerberg, probably won=E2=80=99t be getting back to the P=
ost newsroom anytime soon.
Indeed, many of these folks still don=E2=80=99t seem to understand that the=
y don=E2=80=99t necessarily fit into Bezos=E2=80=99s vision for the paper=
=E2=80=99s future (such as it is). And they also don=E2=80=99t quite realiz=
e that signing some boss-bashing petition and leaking it to Folkenflik isn=
=E2=80=99t how adults actually negotiate or even conduct constructive conve=
rsations.=C2=A0

Furthermore, and rather depressingly, they=E2=80=99ve also engaged in a ver=
sion of this interplay numerous times before, only to be reminded
that Bezos picked Lewis to lead his company, stands by the guy, and has eff=
ectively welcomed them to leave if they don=E2=80=99t like it. (Yes, indeed=
, many have.) At the same time, I also get why so many Posties feel helples=
s, given that Will doesn=E2=80=99t really talk to them, either. But=E2=80=
=94and I=E2=80=99m not sure this is quite a silver lining=E2=80=94the next =
guy probably wouldn=E2=80=99t be much different.
* Lizza lives on: Politico has tapped Jack
Blanchard, its London Playbook editor and author, to move to Washington and=
 take the helm of the flagship morning tip sheet, with help from current Pl=
aybook co-author Eugene Daniels and contributions from a number of the news=
 site=E2=80=99s top reporters, including Jonathan Martin, Dasha Burns, and =
Rachel Bade. Buried down beneath that news was the announcement that Ryan L=
izza will be staying at
Politico=E2=80=94despite his infamous and very unbecoming legal battle with=
 former fianc=C3=A9e and former New York political reporter Olivia Nuzzi=E2=
=80=94as a contributor to its magazine.
* CBS News blues, cont=E2=80=99d: On the heels of damning criticism from An=
ti-Defamation League C.E.O. Jonathan Greenblatt over a recent 60 Minutes pa=
ckage on the Israel-Gaza conflict, CBS News has enlisted former network pre=
sident
Susan Zirinsky to serve as interim executive editor, overseeing standards a=
nd ensuring =E2=80=9Cbalanced, accurate, fair and timely reporting.=E2=80=
=9D While CBS News C.E.O. Wendy McMahon had been looking for someone to tak=
e on this position for some time, I=E2=80=99m told the directive to name Zi=
rinsky, and to do so now, came directly from Shari Redstone, a pro-Israel s=
talwart who has taken issue with the network=E2=80=99s framing of the confl=
ict in the
past. (Remember the Tony Dokoupil=E2=80=93Ta-Nehisi Coates affair?)=C2=A0

Shari praised McMahon=E2=80=99s choice this week, saying she was confident =
Zirinsky would maintain the =E2=80=9Chighest standards in reporting as the =
search continues for a permanent executive editor.=E2=80=9D (Coincidentally=
, I=E2=80=99ve learned that Shari has been seeing Pulitzer-winning former a=
rchitecture critic Paul Goldberger. Perhaps he offered some counsel? Anothe=
r coincidence: McMahon was
Greenblatt=E2=80=99s plus-one at an ADL dinner in November.) Meanwhile, a C=
BS News insider tells me that the 60 Minutes producers are standing by thei=
r reporting. And, of course, the Ellison-RedBird deal for Paramount is expe=
cted to close next quarter.
